{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566601","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566601"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:44:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:44:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18853"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18853","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18853"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.86,0.04,0.02,0.01,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11586"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79734"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11586","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11586"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18853"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65038"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11305"},{"type":"tags","id":"11307"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27262"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27263"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79734","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79734"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor notices that one of their colleagues is regularly being excluded from team activities, subjected to excessive criticism during ward rounds, and given unreasonable deadlines by a senior staff member. This behavior has been ongoing for several months, and the affected colleague appears increasingly distressed.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial action for the junior doctor to take?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Encourage documentation and formal reporting","Discuss the situation with other junior colleagues only","Suggest the affected colleague transfer to another department","Wait to see if the behavior resolves spontaneously","Directly confront the senior staff member"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate initial action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eencourage documentation and formal reporting\u003C/strong\u003E. This ensures the situation is properly recorded and addressed through official channels, while providing evidence for investigation. Documentation should include dates, times, witnesses, and specific incidents.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiscuss the situation with other junior colleagues only\u003C/strong\u003E - While seeking peer support is important, discussing the situation only with colleagues does not address the problem through appropriate channels\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuggest the affected colleague transfer to another department\u003C/strong\u003E - This places the burden on the victim rather than addressing the underlying problem\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWait to see if the behavior resolves spontaneously\u003C/strong\u003E - Bullying behavior typically escalates if not addressed and can have serious psychological consequences\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly confront the senior staff member\u003C/strong\u003E - This may escalate the situation and could put the junior doctor at risk of becoming a target themselves\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare organizations have clear policies and procedures for reporting bullying behavior. These typically involve documenting incidents, reporting to designated officers (such as supervisors, human resources, or workplace health and safety representatives), and accessing support services. Early intervention is crucial to prevent escalation and maintain a safe working environment.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Bullying in healthcare settings is characterized by repeated, unreasonable behavior directed towards workers that creates a risk to health and safety.","Healthcare organizations have a legal and ethical obligation to prevent workplace bullying and maintain a safe working environment.","Effective responses to bullying include documenting incidents, reporting through appropriate channels, and seeking support from designated officers."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Averbuch T, Eliya Y, Van Spall HGC. Systematic review of academic bullying in medical settings: dynamics and consequences. BMJ Open. 2021 Jul 12;11(7):e043256. doi: 10.1136/bmjopen-2020-043256. PMID: 34253657; PMCID: PMC8311313. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8311313/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65038"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18853"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65038","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65038"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T13:48:39+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T13:49:22+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11586"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79734"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":